trans-unit.source: Defines configuration settings that are used to support the compilation infrastructure of Web applications.
This class cannot be inherited.
The CompilationSection class provides a way to programmatically access and modify the content of the `compilation` section of the configuration file.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.CompilationSection"></xref> class by using default settings.
The CompilationSection constructor is not intended to be used directly from your code.
It is called by the ASP.NET configuration system.
You can obtain an instance of the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.CompilationSection> class by using the <xref:System.Configuration.Configuration.GetSection%2A> method.
Gets the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.AssemblyCollection"></xref> of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.CompilationSection"></xref>.
This property contains the assembly references to use during compilation of a dynamic ASP.NET resource.
ASP.NET automatically links these assemblies to the resource when compiling each code module.
A <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.AssemblyCollection"></xref> that contains the assembly objects used during compilation of an ASP.NET resource.
Gets or sets a value specifying a post-process compilation step for an assembly.
A string value specifying the post-process compilation step for an assembly.
Gets or sets a value indicating whether batch compilation is attempted.
Set this attribute to `true` to change the delay caused by the required compilation when you access an uncompiled file.
Setting this attribute to `true` instructs ASP.NET to precompile all the uncompiled files in batch mode.
A delay occurs when the files are first compiled; however once the files are compiled, the delay is eliminated.
<xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if batch compilation is attempted; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
The default is <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref>.
Gets or sets the time-out period, in seconds, for batch compilation.
Indicates the time-out period, in seconds, for batch compilation.
If the compilation cannot be completed within the time-out period, the compiler reverts to single-compilation mode for the current page.
A value indicating the amount of time in seconds granted for batch compilation to occur.
Gets the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.BuildProviderCollection"></xref> collection of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.CompilationSection"></xref> class.
A <xref:System.Web.Compilation.BuildProvider> object provides the functionality to parse a specific file type and to generate code from that file.
A <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.BuildProviderCollection"></xref> that contains the build providers used during a compilation.
Gets the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.CodeSubDirectoriesCollection"></xref> of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.CompilationSection"></xref>.
This property defines an ordered collection of subdirectories containing files compiled at run time.
There can be any number of subdirectories.
A <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.CodeSubDirectoriesCollection"></xref> collection that contains an ordered collection of subdirectories containing files compiled at run time.
Gets the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.CompilerCollection"></xref> collection of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.CompilationSection"></xref> class.
The Compilers property does not refer to any actual element in the underlying configuration file.
It is a construct that allows easy access to the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.Compiler> objects it contains.
A <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.CompilerCollection"></xref> collection that contains a collection of <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.Compiler"></xref> objects.
Gets or sets a string representing the object type used to intercept a <xref href="System.Web.UI.ControlBuilder"></xref> object and configure a container.
A string representing the object type used to intercept a <xref href="System.Web.UI.ControlBuilder"></xref> object.
Gets or sets a value specifying whether to compile release binaries or debug binaries.
<xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if debug binaries will be used for compilation; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
<xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref> specifies that release binaries will be used for compilation.
The default is <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
Gets or sets the default programming language to use in dynamic-compilation files.
Specifies the default programming language, such as C# or VB.NET, to use in dynamic compilation files.
Language names are defined using the `system.codedom` section.
The default programming language is `vb`, which specifies VB.NET as the default programming language.
A value specifying the default programming language to use in dynamic-compilation files.
Gets or sets whether the "disableObsoleteWarnings" configuration value in the Compilation section is set.

<xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the "disableObsoleteWarnings" configuration value in the Compilation section is set; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
Gets or sets a value that indicates whether an ASP.NET application can take advantage of [!INCLUDE[win8](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] prefetch functionality.
Prefetch is a utility that is intended to improve application startup performance by loading application data into memory before it is demanded .
> [!NOTE] > The [!INCLUDE[win8](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] prefetch service must be configured and running for this setting to be effective.

<xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if an ASP.NET application can take advantage of [!INCLUDE[win8](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)] prefetch functionality; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
The default is <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
Gets or sets a value indicating whether to use the Microsoft Visual Basic <xref uid="langword_csharp_explicit" name="explicit" href=""></xref> compile option.
This property specifies the setting of the Microsoft Visual Basic `explicit` compile option.
When set to `true`, the Visual Basic `explicit` compile option is enabled.
When the option is enabled, all variables must be explicitly declared using a `Dim`, `Private`, `Public`, or `ReDim` statement.
The default is `true`.

<xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the Visual Basic <xref uid="langword_csharp_explicit" name="explicit" href=""></xref> compile option is enabled; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
<xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref> specifies that the Visual Basic <xref uid="langword_csharp_explicit" name="explicit" href=""></xref> compile option is disabled.
The default is <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref>.
Gets the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ExpressionBuilderCollection"></xref> of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.CompilationSection"></xref>.
A <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ExpressionBuilderCollection"></xref> that contains <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ExpressionBuilder"></xref> objects.

Gets the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.FolderLevelBuildProviderCollection"></xref> collection of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.CompilationSection"></xref> class, which represents the build providers that are used during compilation.
A <xref:System.Web.Configuration.FolderLevelBuildProvider> object provides the functionality to parse a particular file type and to generate code from that file.
The build providers that are used during compilation.
To be added.
Gets or sets the maximum combined size of the generated source files per batched compilation.
Specifies the maximum size (in kilobytes) of the generated source files per batched compilation.
The default value is 1000 KB.
An integer value indicating the maximum combined size of the generated source files per batched compilation.
Gets or sets the maximum number of pages per batched compilation.
An integer value indicating the maximum number of pages that will be compiled into a single batch.
The default number of pages is 1000.
Gets or sets whether the " maxConcurrentCompilations" configuration value in the Compilation section is set.

<xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the " maxConcurrentCompilations" configuration value in the Compilation section is set; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
Gets or sets the number of dynamic recompiles of resources that can occur before the application restarts.
Indicates the number of dynamic recompiles of resources that can occur before the application restarts.
This attribute is supported at the global and application configuration levels, but not at the directory configuration level.
> [!NOTE] > ASP.NET increases the NumRecompilesBeforeAppRestart property value every time an assembly is invalidated and fails to be deleted.
A value indicating the number of dynamic recompiles of resources that can occur before the application restarts.
The default is 15 recompilations.
Gets or sets a value that indicates whether the compilation must be optimized.
<xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the compilation must be optimized; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
The default is <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
Gets or sets a value that indicates whether the application is optimized for the deployed environment.

When this property is set to <xref:System.Web.Configuration.ProfileGuidedOptimizationsFlags>, the ASP.NET compilation system enables optimizations that are intended to speed up ASP.NET startup performance at the expense of increased CPU utilization.
The default setting for this property is <xref:System.Web.Configuration.ProfileGuidedOptimizationsFlags>.
A value that indicates whether the application is optimized for the deployed environment.
To be added.
Gets or sets the Visual Basic <xref uid="langword_csharp_strict" name="strict" href=""></xref> compile option.
When `true`, compilation explicitly disallows any data-type conversions in which data loss would occur, and any conversion between numeric types and strings.

<xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the Visual Basic <xref uid="langword_csharp_strict" name="strict" href=""></xref> compile option is used; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
The default is <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref>.
Gets or sets the version of the .NET Framework that the Web site targets.
For information about how to target a specific version of the .NET Framework, see [.NET Framework Multi-Targeting for ASP.NET Web Projects](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
The version of the .NET Framework that the Web site targets.
The default value is <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref>.
Gets or sets a value that specifies the directory to use for temporary file storage during compilation.
A value specifying the directory to use for temporary file storage during compilation.
Gets or sets a value indicating whether instructions to the compiler use physical paths or URLs.
If this property is specified as `true` in the configuration, URLs will be used for the compiler instructions instead of physical paths.

<xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if instructions to the compiler use URLs rather than physical paths; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
The default is <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
